rsDhcpMIB.name: rsDhcpMIB

revisions.description: Added number of clients statistcs objects

rsDhcpMIB.contactinfo: Riverstone Networks, Inc 5200 Great America Parkway Santa Clara, CA 95054 (408) 878-6500 nms-eng@riverstonenet.com http://www.riverstonenet.com
rsDhcpMIB.description: This mib module defines an SNMP API to manage Riverstone switch DHCP feature

RsErrorCode.name: RsErrorCode
RsErrorCode.description: A unique value, greater than zero defining the operation completion status.

rsDhcpLeaseFileGroup.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileGroup
rsDhcpLeaseFileGroup.description: Group for dhcp lease file upload

rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp
rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp.description: Transfer operation to be performed. DHCP lease files are ASCII NVT text files. Send operations use tftp to transfer a file from the manager to agent. Receive operations use tftp to transfer the file from the agent to the manager. Default value is no operation or noop.

rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddressType.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddressType
rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddressType.description: Specifies the type of IP address of the Manager to be used by the agent for rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp operations.

rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddress.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddress
rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddress.description: The IP address of the Manager to be used by the agent for rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp operations. Address must be a unicast address that is reachable from the agent and no firewalls/acls preventing tftp datagrams from being transferred. The address type is determined by the object value of rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddressType. A value for this object MUST be set prior to setting rsDhcpLeaseFileActivateTransfer to TRUE.

rsDhcpLeaseFileFileName.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileFileName
rsDhcpLeaseFileFileName.description: The file name to be retrieved from the tftp server at host dhcpLeaseFileManagerAddress or to be written to. Default value is blank. Length of filename string must not exceed 255 alpha-numeric characters, no spaces in filenames.

rsDhcpLeaseFileActivateTransfer.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileActivateTransfer
rsDhcpLeaseFileActivateTransfer.description: Activate the file transfer operation with a value of True(1) or stop it with False(2). Poll rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferStatus for current status. Default value is False. rsDhcpLeaseFileFileName, rsDhcpLeaseFileManagerAddress and rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferOp must be valid prior to setting this object to True.

rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferStatus.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferStatus
rsDhcpLeaseFileTransferStatus.description: The current status of the transfer task. Default state is idle. sending indicates a file transfer (agent->mgr) in progress. receiving indicates sending a file from Manager to agent. transferComplete indicates a successful transfer. error indicates a failed transfer. See rsDhcpLeaseFileLastError to diagnose why the transfer failed.

rsDhcpLeaseFileLastError.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileLastError
rsDhcpLeaseFileLastError.description: A reason code for the last transfer operation. Poll this value when doing sets against dhcpLeaseFileActivateFile obtain status.

rsDhcpLeaseFileLastErrorReason.name: rsDhcpLeaseFileLastErrorReason
rsDhcpLeaseFileLastErrorReason.description: A string representation of dhcpLeaseFileLastError which may contain additional details.

rsDhcpMaxClientsAllowed.name: rsDhcpMaxClientsAllowed
rsDhcpMaxClientsAllowed.description: Maximum number of DHCP clients allowed per system

rsDhcpNumberOfClients.name: rsDhcpNumberOfClients
rsDhcpNumberOfClients.description: Current number of DHCP clients connected

rsDhcpCompliance.name: rsDhcpCompliance
rsDhcpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the dhcp management and config objects for RS

rsDhcpGroup1.name: rsDhcpGroup1
rsDhcpGroup1.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent version 1.0 of DHCP MIB

rsDhcpGroup2.name: rsDhcpGroup2
rsDhcpGroup2.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent version 1.1 of DHCP MIB
